<br>
The Virral Triumvirate Egg suggestion, while accurate, is a bit misleading since they run about 70 million each, and most folks can't afford 'em. So don't spend too much time trying to locate one of those. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The Q22-Q25 <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://auno.org/ao/db.php?cmd=view&amp;id=124147&amp;t=ag">OT-Windchaser M06 Quartz</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> adds +10 treatment and even +8 stamina, so it's a must have.  Lots of low level folks blitz for them (Q22 is best for non-rifle users), so you should be able to buy one fairly easily.<br>
<br>
Feline Grace and Enhanced Senses (both low level agent buffs) will also add another +3 pts or so, since Treatment is based upon Int, Agil and Sense.  Similarly, you'll want +12 Int, +12 Agil and +12 Sense running, too.<br>
<br>
Temporary implants are the best way to &quot;ramp up&quot; your treatment, but using them means your final Rt Hand, Eye and/or Head cannot be as high as your other implants, since those 3 are the treatment implants, and if you need to have them in to place the others, you get &quot;stuck&quot; with lower treatment after you pull them out to put your real ones in.<br>
<br>
If you can't find a doc for +80, there is an adventurer buff (Robust Treatment) that adds +60 treatment, but its even more rare than finding the doc with +80.<br>
<br>
Finally, the tradeskill <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://auno.org/ao/db.php?cmd=view&amp;id=161770&amp;t=ag">Treatment Library</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> mentioned varies from +2 to +18 according to QL (1-200), and it requires both Comp Lit and Treatment to equip.  You'll need someone with Breaking &amp; Entering and Nano Programming to make one for you (iirc), such as an Engie, Trader, Doc, or maybe an MP.  It's relatively easy to buy the parts needed to create one in the Q70-Q120 range, however.<br>
<br>
Since OmniMed clothes cover everything but head and back, a Biomech Armor Helm and Biomech Armor Cloak can get you a few more points.  They require Psychic and Stamina, so for an MA it shouldn't be hard to equip them (MA skill is 30% Psychic, so it shouldn't be neglected!), and the Biomech parts add roughly +1 treatment for every 20 QL.  Note, however, that I've never seen them lower than Q75, so they may not be in the game lower than that (kinda like Omni Pol Elite that way).  Q75 requires 211 Psychic, 193 Stamina, and adds +4 treatment for each piece.  Q80 will net you +5 each, btw.<br>
<br>
Finally, since they fixed that infinite treatment stationary clinic bug we all enjoyed &quot;back in the day&quot;, you simply are going to HAVE to keep treatment maxed.  Implants are vital for MAs since we can't overequip a weapon like other classes, so keep that treatment maxed and keep those implants up-to-date.<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
